{"questionId":"13110","questionHtml":"<p>Write down the transformation that will transform the graph of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = p\\left( x \\right)\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mi>p</mi> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mi>x</mi> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span> onto the graph&nbsp;of&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = 8{x^3} + 12{x^2} + 16x - 24\"><mi>y</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>3</mn></msup><mo>−</mo><mn>12</mn><msup><mi>x</mi><mn>2</mn></msup><mo>+</mo><mn>16</mn><mi>x</mi><mo>−</mo><mn>24</mn></math></span>.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p>new graph is&nbsp;<span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"y = p\\left( {2x} \\right)\"> <mi>y</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mi>p</mi> <mrow> <mo>(</mo> <mrow> <mn>2</mn> <mi>x</mi> </mrow> <mo>)</mo> </mrow> </math></span>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p>stretch parallel to the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"> <mi>x</mi> </math></span>-axis (with <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x = 0\"> <mi>x</mi> <mo>=</mo> <mn>0</mn> </math></span> invariant), scale factor 0.5 &nbsp; &nbsp;<em><strong>A</strong><strong>1</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>Note:</strong> Accept “horizontal” instead of “parallel to the <span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x\"> <mi>x</mi> </math></span>-axis”.</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"13110","referenceCode":"19M.1.AHL.TZ1.H_10c","subjectId":"51-dp-mathematics-applications-and-interpretation","title":"Write down the transformation that will transform the graph of y = p ( x ) onto the graph of y=8x3−12x2+16x−24.","paper":"1","level":"AHL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 4—